Getting Orange multicat-supervisor
================

Orange released multicat-supervisor versions can be downloaded at:
https://github.com/orange-tv-blagnac/multicat-supervisor

Multicat-supervisor is developed using git. To get the latest version, clone
the repository at: git://github.com/orange-tv-blagnac/multicat-supervisor.git


Basic configurations
====================

Multicat-supervisor tool configuration shall be done from multicat.ini file.

[SUPERVISOR] block stands for StreamManager database configuration.
[NETWORK] block stands for network TTL configuration.

For advanced configuration, refer to admin documentation.
https://github.com/orange-tv-blagnac/newtv-ip-streamer


Installing Orange multicat-supervisor
===================

Compile the program with `make` and install with `make install`.

Refer to admin documentation for libraries installation
https://github.com/orange-tv-blagnac/newtv-ip-streamer


Basic uses
==========

Only one instance by OS shall be launched.

Starting multicat-supervisor

/usr/local/multicat-tools/sh/multicat-supervisor start

Stoping multicat-supervisor

/usr/local/multicat-tools/sh/multicat-supervisor stop

Multicat-supervisor tool shall be use with StreamManager tool (HMI).
https://github.com/orange-tv-blagnac/stream-manager

Refer to StreamManager user and admin documentation
https://github.com/orange-tv-blagnac/newtv-ip-streamer
